gomodel:SYNGO_2261  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Immunogold labeling of the δ and α2 subunits of the GABAA receptor. Gold particles that indicate the location of the δ subunit (A-D, arrows) were present on or near the plasma membrane of dendrites (D) that were in contact with axon terminals (T). Gold particles were localized primarily at perisynaptic sites, just outside or at the outer edge of symmetric synapses (A, D, solid arrowheads).\". Experimental description: - \"Tissue preparation for microscopy. Mice were deeply anesthetized with sodium...\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
